# Git Conventions

## Conventional Commits

All commits MUST follow the [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) specification. Allowed types: `fix`, `feat`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `revert`, `ci`, `build`, `release`.

## Branch Naming

- Feature branches: `<JIRA-ID>-short-description` (e.g., `CAREN-1234-add-vpc-support`)
- Non-feature branches: use a short descriptive prefix (e.g., `fix/typo-in-readme`, `build/update-deps`)

## Commit and PR Titles

Format: `<type>: [<JIRA-ID>] Title`

Examples:
- `feat: [CAREN-1234] Add VPC configuration support`
- `fix: [CAREN-5678] Resolve nil pointer in handler`
- `build: Update Go dependencies` (no Jira ID needed for non-feature work)

Constraints:
- Title MUST be <= 72 characters total.
- Do NOT end the title with a period.

## Commit Body

- Wrap lines at 120 characters.
- Explain *why* the change was made, not *what* changed (the diff shows that).
- Separate title from body with a blank line.
